WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.038 --> 00:00:06.507
[dramatic music]

2
00:00:06.540 --> 00:00:08.709
[Will] I'm going to make
a traditional ivrulik.

3
00:00:08.742 --> 00:00:11.178
We're in one of the most
desolate climates on Earth.

4
00:00:11.278 --> 00:00:13.080
You're not going
to survive a winter

5
00:00:13.113 --> 00:00:14.882
without a strong shelter.

6
00:00:14.882 --> 00:00:16.116
All right.

7
00:00:16.116 --> 00:00:17.417
A dead squirrel over there.

8
00:00:17.451 --> 00:00:19.486
♪

9
00:00:19.520 --> 00:00:22.556
[thudding]

10
00:00:22.589 --> 00:00:24.725
What the [bleep]?

11
00:00:24.725 --> 00:00:26.527
That's embarrassing.

12
00:00:28.629 --> 00:00:30.531
♪

13
00:00:35.602 --> 00:00:36.737
Wow.

14
00:00:36.837 --> 00:00:39.406
That moose will live
for another day.

15
00:00:39.439 --> 00:00:40.707
[popping]

16
00:00:40.741 --> 00:00:42.142
- What was that?

17
00:00:42.242 --> 00:00:46.013
Oh. [bleep].
My ferro rod's on fire.

18
00:00:46.046 --> 00:00:47.214
- Bow and drill

19
00:00:47.247 --> 00:00:49.283
is not one of my best skills.

20
00:00:49.316 --> 00:00:52.753
♪

21
00:00:52.786 --> 00:00:54.354
[sighs]

22
00:00:54.388 --> 00:00:55.789
I'm in the Arctic.

23
00:00:55.889 --> 00:00:58.325
I gotta have fire.

24
00:00:58.358 --> 00:00:59.660
- Come up.

25
00:00:59.693 --> 00:01:00.928
- [grunts]

26
00:01:00.961 --> 00:01:01.962
[bleep]

27
00:01:01.995 --> 00:01:05.532
♪

28
00:01:05.566 --> 00:01:08.168
- Fire!

29
00:01:08.201 --> 00:01:09.202
[David] This is David Booth.

30
00:01:09.236 --> 00:01:10.370
I'm officially tapping out.

31
00:01:10.404 --> 00:01:12.573
♪

32
00:01:12.606 --> 00:01:15.509
[dramatic music]

33
00:01:15.576 --> 00:01:22.616
♪

34
00:01:27.120 --> 00:01:34.127
♪

35
00:01:47.040 --> 00:01:49.209
[Will] OK. I've been working
hard on this ivrulik.

36
00:01:49.242 --> 00:01:51.912
and my feet.
they're just getting hot.

37
00:01:52.012 --> 00:01:54.681
They're getting hot
and they're getting stinky.

38
00:01:54.715 --> 00:01:57.451
And one of the things that
we've done traditionally.

39
00:01:57.484 --> 00:02:00.354
when that happens. when you
get hot and stinky feet.

40
00:02:00.387 --> 00:02:04.124
is you put ptarmigan feathers
in your boot.

41
00:02:04.157 --> 00:02:09.096
And in this case.
I'll use my grouse feathers.

42
00:02:09.128 --> 00:02:11.765
Oof. stinks.

43
00:02:11.798 --> 00:02:14.167
Take our boots here.

44
00:02:14.201 --> 00:02:16.937
Got some clean.

45
00:02:16.970 --> 00:02:18.872
non-wet feathers.

46
00:02:18.972 --> 00:02:20.807
and we'll just stick them
in the boot.

47
00:02:24.511 --> 00:02:25.846
Just like that.

48
00:02:28.548 --> 00:02:30.350
We'll stick those in there

49
00:02:30.384 --> 00:02:32.753
and push them towards the end.

50
00:02:32.786 --> 00:02:35.122
OK. I think that'll do.

51
00:02:37.057 --> 00:02:38.859
All right.
That should take the stench out

52
00:02:38.892 --> 00:02:41.528
of my boot and out of my socks.

53
00:02:41.561 --> 00:02:48.568
♪

54
00:02:49.803 --> 00:02:53.507
Ukalliatchiaq translates
to snowshoe hare

55
00:02:53.607 --> 00:02:57.444
in the Iñupiaq
Kobuk River dialect.

56
00:03:03.483 --> 00:03:05.852
So...

57
00:03:05.886 --> 00:03:09.256
winter is coming.

58
00:03:09.356 --> 00:03:12.826
The Iñupiaq language.
it's an endangered language.

59
00:03:12.926 --> 00:03:16.196
There's upwards of 20.000
of us in the world.

60
00:03:16.196 --> 00:03:19.166
And I feel like
the Iñupiaq way of life

61
00:03:19.199 --> 00:03:21.802
is just kind of fading away
with the technology

62
00:03:21.835 --> 00:03:24.204
that we're given.

63
00:03:24.204 --> 00:03:29.042
So I'm looking for new signs
of game on the riverbank here.

64
00:03:29.076 --> 00:03:31.078
I'm not seeing any.

65
00:03:31.078 --> 00:03:34.481
We've definitely had
a bump up in technology

66
00:03:34.481 --> 00:03:36.316
in Kotzebue
in the last ten years.

67
00:03:36.349 --> 00:03:38.151
The phone just started
to come out.

68
00:03:38.185 --> 00:03:41.254
High-tech video game system
just started to come out.

69
00:03:41.354 --> 00:03:44.758
And so I'm seeing a lot of
kids just want to stay home

70
00:03:44.791 --> 00:03:48.061
and do those types of things.

71
00:03:48.161 --> 00:03:51.998
You don't even see as many
children playing out anymore.

72
00:03:52.032 --> 00:03:54.201
They want to be like
the people that they're seeing

73
00:03:54.234 --> 00:03:57.437
on their tablets and phones
and TVs and all that.

74
00:03:57.437 --> 00:03:59.973
And that's not
the Iñupiaq people.

75
00:04:00.006 --> 00:04:02.375
It's tough to see.

76
00:04:06.213 --> 00:04:09.216
[rustling]

77
00:04:11.885 --> 00:04:13.887
Nothing in here today.

78
00:04:20.560 --> 00:04:23.597
I had one right here.

79
00:04:23.630 --> 00:04:26.166
Took the whole wire with it.

80
00:04:26.199 --> 00:04:27.801
Damn.

81
00:04:27.834 --> 00:04:29.169
Moose. possibly.

82
00:04:32.439 --> 00:04:35.041
So let's be quiet.

83
00:04:35.075 --> 00:04:36.510
Let's check the next one.

84
00:04:36.543 --> 00:04:38.712
♪

85
00:04:42.182 --> 00:04:44.751
Beautiful.
beautiful. beautiful.

86
00:04:44.851 --> 00:04:46.953
Caught a rabbit.

87
00:04:46.987 --> 00:04:49.856
Caught a ukalliatchiaq.

88
00:04:49.890 --> 00:04:53.326
[speaking Iñupiaq]

89
00:04:53.326 --> 00:04:56.396
Oh. man.

90
00:04:56.396 --> 00:04:58.732
Much needed.

91
00:04:58.765 --> 00:05:00.667
Got him.

92
00:05:00.767 --> 00:05:02.502
Yes. we're eating.

93
00:05:02.602 --> 00:05:05.405
Eating good. eating good.

94
00:05:05.438 --> 00:05:07.841
That's a lot of meat compared
to what I got right now.

95
00:05:08.942 --> 00:05:12.712
This is going to last me
a few more days.

96
00:05:12.813 --> 00:05:15.782
Getting closer
to gill net time.

97
00:05:15.882 --> 00:05:17.584
Beautiful.

98
00:05:17.617 --> 00:05:21.688
We'll get back and make
some ukalliatchiaq soup.

99
00:05:21.721 --> 00:05:26.560
♪

100
00:05:26.560 --> 00:05:27.627
[sighs]

101
00:05:27.661 --> 00:05:30.330
There's my stomach rumbling.

102
00:05:30.363 --> 00:05:32.332
Get the rabbit skin first.

103
00:05:32.365 --> 00:05:34.067
and then start a fire second.

104
00:05:34.134 --> 00:05:37.070
♪

105
00:05:37.070 --> 00:05:41.074
Make sure the whole bunny's
in the picture.

106
00:05:41.074 --> 00:05:42.475
OK.

107
00:05:43.910 --> 00:05:46.413
Down...

108
00:05:46.446 --> 00:05:49.482
between the middle
of the legs.

109
00:05:49.516 --> 00:05:53.220
Cut around the...

110
00:05:53.253 --> 00:05:55.388
ankle area.

111
00:05:55.422 --> 00:06:00.594
Being out here. I feel like
this has given me purpose.

112
00:06:00.594 --> 00:06:02.796
I'll do the front paws.

113
00:06:02.829 --> 00:06:05.599
I definitely feel like
there's a lack of role model

114
00:06:05.599 --> 00:06:07.667
for the Iñupiaq children.

115
00:06:07.701 --> 00:06:11.371
If you start to get
any tension.

116
00:06:11.404 --> 00:06:15.242
just a little bit of a trim.

117
00:06:15.242 --> 00:06:17.844
I want my culture to survive.

118
00:06:17.878 --> 00:06:19.613
And that's it.

119
00:06:19.646 --> 00:06:22.315
And we'll gut.

120
00:06:22.349 --> 00:06:24.484
We'll pull these

121
00:06:24.484 --> 00:06:26.653
guts out here.

122
00:06:26.686 --> 00:06:29.089
Get a fire going.
get it in the pot.

123
00:06:30.223 --> 00:06:32.926
And. uh. yeah.

124
00:06:35.061 --> 00:06:39.366
Get some
ukalliatchiaq soup cooking.

125
00:06:39.399 --> 00:06:46.439
♪

126
00:06:56.149 --> 00:06:58.084
With ashes.

127
00:07:07.794 --> 00:07:12.933
Now I will use this to brush.

128
00:07:18.004 --> 00:07:19.005
All right.

129
00:07:19.005 --> 00:07:20.707
Are you looking at this?

130
00:07:22.976 --> 00:07:25.211
Yeah.

131
00:07:25.245 --> 00:07:26.780
It's better now.

132
00:07:26.813 --> 00:07:28.882
Yeah.

133
00:07:28.882 --> 00:07:33.119
You can make--
you can make signals

134
00:07:33.153 --> 00:07:35.355
to rescue.

135
00:07:35.388 --> 00:07:37.891
Not yet.
Maybe in Christmas.

136
00:07:38.758 --> 00:07:39.993
[lid clangs]

137
00:07:40.026 --> 00:07:42.495
Now what I will do.

138
00:07:42.529 --> 00:07:45.231
I want to try fish something.

139
00:07:45.265 --> 00:07:50.303
♪

140
00:07:50.403 --> 00:07:52.038
I have lot of things to do.

141
00:07:52.072 --> 00:07:54.641
I have my shelter to finish.

142
00:07:54.674 --> 00:07:57.711
But fishing is
the most important thing

143
00:07:57.744 --> 00:07:59.846
in "Alone" season.

144
00:07:59.879 --> 00:08:02.716
Let's get some bait.

145
00:08:03.950 --> 00:08:10.357
Oh. I got all the guts
for fishing.

146
00:08:10.390 --> 00:08:13.360
The one who fish more
is the one

147
00:08:13.360 --> 00:08:16.262
that have more possibilities.
because the fish

148
00:08:16.363 --> 00:08:20.700
will feed the body with more
nutrients than the meat.

149
00:08:20.800 --> 00:08:24.237
I want a big fish.

150
00:08:24.270 --> 00:08:27.273
Yeah. nice throw.

151
00:08:27.273 --> 00:08:32.345
I saw in the other seasons.
people have big animals

152
00:08:32.445 --> 00:08:38.284
and they get thin because
they only eat meat.

153
00:08:46.359 --> 00:08:48.094
Don't get me wrong.

154
00:08:48.128 --> 00:08:51.765
Animal meat is
important to survive.

155
00:08:51.798 --> 00:08:54.401
But protein is not enough.

156
00:08:54.401 --> 00:08:55.835
You need to have fat.

157
00:08:55.835 --> 00:09:00.206
And fish have more fat than
the meat of the animal.

158
00:09:01.941 --> 00:09:06.179
Oh. God bless me
with a big fish.

159
00:09:06.212 --> 00:09:13.153
♪

160
00:09:13.253 --> 00:09:15.288
Nothing.

161
00:09:15.321 --> 00:09:17.357
Yeah.

162
00:09:17.357 --> 00:09:19.292
There's nothing.

163
00:09:20.527 --> 00:09:24.764
I will do a box

164
00:09:24.764 --> 00:09:26.800
to put berries.

165
00:09:26.833 --> 00:09:28.568
waiting for a fish.

166
00:09:28.601 --> 00:09:31.304
♪

167
00:09:31.404 --> 00:09:35.141
The people in Portugal
are strong.

168
00:09:35.241 --> 00:09:38.244
We were made for war.

169
00:09:38.244 --> 00:09:41.648
My strength comes
from when I was young.

170
00:09:49.289 --> 00:09:51.624
It was difficult to breathe.

171
00:09:51.724 --> 00:09:54.327
I damaged my knife.

172
00:09:54.360 --> 00:09:56.229
cutting wire.

173
00:09:56.229 --> 00:09:59.799
I had this inhaler
and I was ashamed

174
00:09:59.833 --> 00:10:02.435
to use it because I feel weak.

175
00:10:02.469 --> 00:10:05.004
People made bullying.

176
00:10:05.038 --> 00:10:09.075
but I start
to play soccer in a team

177
00:10:09.075 --> 00:10:11.111
and develop more discipline.

178
00:10:11.111 --> 00:10:16.349
And I saw that more I train.
more get better.

179
00:10:16.382 --> 00:10:20.186
I want to fight
against everything.

180
00:10:20.220 --> 00:10:24.457
And I'm grateful because
all those things

181
00:10:24.557 --> 00:10:27.560
brought me here
to this moment.

182
00:10:46.112 --> 00:10:53.119
♪

183
00:11:04.397 --> 00:11:11.104
♪

184
00:11:11.204 --> 00:11:12.872
Holy [bleep].

185
00:11:12.972 --> 00:11:17.577
♪

186
00:11:17.610 --> 00:11:19.312
It's the moose.

187
00:11:19.379 --> 00:11:26.419
♪

188
00:11:29.522 --> 00:11:30.957
[tense music]

189
00:11:30.990 --> 00:11:32.892
[Pedrosa] Holy [bleep].

190
00:11:32.926 --> 00:11:34.928
♪

191
00:11:34.961 --> 00:11:37.230
It's the moose.

192
00:11:37.297 --> 00:11:44.337
♪

193
00:11:48.141 --> 00:11:55.148
♪

194
00:12:10.563 --> 00:12:12.565
[breathing heavily]

195
00:12:14.434 --> 00:12:21.074
♪

196
00:12:21.107 --> 00:12:23.309
Can you see the moose?

197
00:12:25.445 --> 00:12:26.646
It's a female.

198
00:12:26.679 --> 00:12:29.115
It's with two childs.

199
00:12:29.148 --> 00:12:33.052
so I cannot hunt them.

200
00:12:33.086 --> 00:12:34.988
But they are awesome.

201
00:12:35.021 --> 00:12:39.926
♪

202
00:12:39.926 --> 00:12:42.395
Wait. wait. wait.

203
00:12:53.539 --> 00:12:55.475
I will try to flank them.

204
00:12:55.508 --> 00:13:02.548
♪

205
00:13:05.485 --> 00:13:12.525
♪

206
00:13:17.630 --> 00:13:19.365
[bleep].

207
00:13:19.365 --> 00:13:21.768
♪

208
00:13:23.770 --> 00:13:30.777
♪

209
00:13:40.953 --> 00:13:42.555
[bleep].

210
00:13:42.555 --> 00:13:45.558
[panting]

211
00:14:04.310 --> 00:14:07.380
[panting]

212
00:14:16.756 --> 00:14:18.758
I'm terrible.

213
00:14:18.791 --> 00:14:20.660
[sighs]

214
00:14:20.693 --> 00:14:23.396
I don't deserve to be here.

215
00:14:23.429 --> 00:14:30.436
♪

216
00:14:32.705 --> 00:14:36.776
Today I missed my chance.

217
00:14:36.809 --> 00:14:38.644
I feel terrible.

218
00:14:41.080 --> 00:14:47.320
First. because I probably
injured that moose.

219
00:14:50.390 --> 00:14:52.692
And I lost one more arrow.

220
00:14:55.161 --> 00:14:59.632
That moose could fill me
here forever.

221
00:14:59.665 --> 00:15:01.367
And I miss my chance.

222
00:15:03.870 --> 00:15:10.910
♪

223
00:15:26.559 --> 00:15:31.964
♪

224
00:15:31.998 --> 00:15:35.868
I want to sleep...

225
00:15:35.902 --> 00:15:40.206
because I lost
my opportunity.

226
00:15:47.046 --> 00:15:48.448
Sorry.

227
00:15:54.053 --> 00:15:59.692
♪

228
00:16:07.099 --> 00:16:08.634
[Poldi] Jeez.

229
00:16:08.634 --> 00:16:11.204
It's a full-time job and some.

230
00:16:13.372 --> 00:16:15.875
Processing fish.

231
00:16:15.908 --> 00:16:19.779
cooking food.

232
00:16:19.812 --> 00:16:21.581
and--[spits]

233
00:16:21.681 --> 00:16:24.217
keeping a smoker going.

234
00:16:26.752 --> 00:16:29.789
So when do we get
to phone in a friend?

235
00:16:29.889 --> 00:16:32.158
Emotionally. I feel like
I'm on an absolute roll

236
00:16:32.191 --> 00:16:33.826
in terms of successes.

237
00:16:33.860 --> 00:16:36.395
The fishing and the snaring
is so effective. you know.

238
00:16:36.429 --> 00:16:39.332
I'm ticking boxes quicker
than I thought I would.

239
00:16:39.365 --> 00:16:41.300
♪

240
00:16:41.400 --> 00:16:43.002
I've got plenty of food.

241
00:16:43.035 --> 00:16:45.304
I'm going to keep
eating three meals a day

242
00:16:45.338 --> 00:16:47.773
so that I can push
myself physically.

243
00:16:47.807 --> 00:16:49.809
And I built the smoker.

244
00:16:49.842 --> 00:16:51.711
Knowing that I've got
myself some reserves

245
00:16:51.811 --> 00:16:54.413
is really. really reassuring.

246
00:16:54.447 --> 00:16:57.350
'Cause. you know. right now
I literally can't fit

247
00:16:57.383 --> 00:17:00.753
any more fish in my stomach.

248
00:17:00.853 --> 00:17:02.655
There it is. folks.

249
00:17:05.491 --> 00:17:07.359
All right. the smoker.

250
00:17:07.393 --> 00:17:10.396
I've got all of the pike
in there. except one.

251
00:17:10.396 --> 00:17:12.964
Which means I can start
on my permanent shelter.

252
00:17:12.999 --> 00:17:15.300
I had so much fun
with this tepee.

253
00:17:15.401 --> 00:17:18.637
I'm going to make my permanent
shelter a tepee as well.

254
00:17:18.671 --> 00:17:25.711
♪

255
00:17:27.946 --> 00:17:30.116
The weather's getting colder.
the wind's blowing

256
00:17:30.149 --> 00:17:31.517
a little bit harder at night.

257
00:17:31.551 --> 00:17:36.923
And I know it's changing
because it's going into winter.

258
00:17:36.956 --> 00:17:38.357
Timber.

259
00:17:38.357 --> 00:17:41.160
[tree cracking]

260
00:17:41.193 --> 00:17:44.964
But it's happening quicker
than I'm expecting.

261
00:17:44.997 --> 00:17:48.901
And it's my first real
sort of sinking feeling of.

262
00:17:48.935 --> 00:17:52.238
like. I need to get
my permanent shelter up.

263
00:17:52.238 --> 00:17:53.839
[tree cracking]

264
00:17:53.873 --> 00:17:55.575
And I've sort of ridden
the high

265
00:17:55.675 --> 00:17:57.677
of figuring out
my food source.

266
00:17:57.710 --> 00:18:00.680
And now I do need
to get my tepee done.

267
00:18:00.680 --> 00:18:03.716
♪

268
00:18:03.749 --> 00:18:06.319
I'm actually having
a lot of fun.

269
00:18:06.352 --> 00:18:07.820
All righty. folks.
we're going to get

270
00:18:07.853 --> 00:18:11.157
this big old log over there.

271
00:18:11.190 --> 00:18:14.527
Going into the competition
with my body weight.

272
00:18:14.560 --> 00:18:16.195
I told myself that
I need a fire

273
00:18:16.228 --> 00:18:18.130
and my permanent shelter
to keep me warm.

274
00:18:18.164 --> 00:18:21.133
So a fire was always a must.

275
00:18:22.301 --> 00:18:26.572
So my plan is to build a large
tepee as my permanent shelter

276
00:18:26.606 --> 00:18:28.874
just because it's basically
a chimney that you live in.

277
00:18:28.874 --> 00:18:31.877
But if you get it nice
and insulated and air-tight.

278
